CatDescriptText: Cutline of article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1959, page A2, reads: "Victory Celebration to Close 'Y' Drive March 2 - The 1959 membership enrollment of the Centre Ave. Branch YMCA will close on March 2, with a victory celebration. The fourth report meeting sent the total members reported to date to 812, for 5,070 points.  Although the goal has been exceeded, the workers have decided to continue their enrollment another week, to reach their 8,000-point goal."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of woman, with six men standing around her, including Byrd Brown on left, gathered in front of membership toteboard inscribed "the Atlas Spaceship," in Centre Avenue YMCA
